What should I do if I cannot edit a very large map
?
Select an edited map data file (json) and select the corresponding basemap

The map editor is based on a browser. The maximum pixel size of a picture supported by the browser is 8192 *8192
If it is larger than this pixel, it cannot be displayed. What if you need to edit a map larger than this limit? 
Follow the following steps to edit a very large map

If you have a 10000 *10000 pixel map that needs to be edited, it will not be displayed if you open it directly with the map editor. You can edit as follows. 

1. Make a thumbnail of this map, for example, set the thumbnail size to 8000 *8000. 
2. Click the editor to create a new map and select the thumbnail in the new interface. 
3. After selecting the thumbnail, enter 10000 and 10000 in the map width and height input box
4. Click OK to edit the 10000 *10000 map. This map is enlarged from the 8000 *8000 thumbnail. . 
5. After editing, click Save to get 10000 *10000 map data
6. Put the map data into the client project. The client background map still uses the original 10000 *10000 image
7. Because the map is too large , it cannot be displayed directly whether it is on a web page or a small game platform such as WeChat
8. The way to solve the problem of displaying this very large map in the game is to load it into parts by cutting the image. The relevant image cutting tool is available for download on this editor page. The front-end game framework comes with a tiled map loading function by default.
